history.text: Hi, did you like this movie?
I like movies about World War II so yes I liked it.
Do you usually watch these kinds of movies?
No I don’t prefer this genre. I’m surprised with all the big scenes that they left out any drama.
I liked that that they used extensive practical effects. The chaos is what made me love it.
Do you think the fact that Harry Styles was a singer made him get the role?
Nolan wasn’t aware of Styles renown as a singer so I would think that wouldn’t affect the decision.
I see. Do you think Aneurin Barnard's role was a difficult one to play?
I must say that with all the horror and realism from the get go this is a period piece I enjoyed more than any other.
Yes I think it was.
Did the small amount of dialogue make you enjoy it more?
I think it helped.
Did you think the role of Tommy was critical?
Yes, without him Alex would've surely died.
Did you feel sorry for George?
Yes he was an innocent young kid.
I felt Tommy and Alex were so lucky they were denied passage onto the boat.
That's true, he seems really lucky. How do you think he felt being the only survivor?
I’d say lucky. They have so many close calls throughout the movie. I was very surprised at Alex’s accusations toward Gibson. Why do you think he did that to him?
I feel that his silence contributed greatly to him being accused. I didn't like that he died though. Do you think Peter was right to lie about George's death?
I don’t know why he lied to the officer about his death.
I particularly liked when the destroyer Tommy and Alex were swimming to got destroyed.
Do you agree with the Rotten Tomato rating?
I do. I think the big scenes in this movie made it worthwhile.
How did you feel about the way the movie ended?
I agree. I think it ended nicely. I'm happy that Alex and Tommy survived. What do you think?
I liked the ending. They were portrayed as heroes
That's true. I think Commander Bolton was brave to remain behind.
Yes I agree. How do you think the soldier felt when he saw George’s body carried out? I think he felt guilty probably.
I think he felt betrayed. At least he was apart of the 300,000 survivors.

I like that Peter went to the local newspaper with a picture of George
. It was a nice way to honor him.
That’s interesting. I think it was good that George was in the paper as a hero his self.
Yes I agree it was.
Do you think it was the same newspaper Tommy was reading?
